  "title": "Recipe Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><p><u><strong>Recipe Specialist</strong></u><br /><br />Responsible for the I&R projects in the factory, new recipe development, introduction of new and improved products as well as maintaining existing products. Support NPTC/Markets with expertise in nutrition science, ensure compliance with Nestlé policies and guidelines .<br /></p><p><u><strong>A day in the life..</strong></u></p><ol><li>Customise nutritional formulations, identify formulation issues and lead improvement action programmes within the plant.</li><li>Timely review data in CAT/DevEX system and carry out necessary corrective and preventive actions. Conduct the evaluation of the raw materials innate data and perform macro/micro ingredient adjustment to optimize the finished product quality.</li><li>Achieve timely completion of recipe review as per schedule. Support product development and renovation to improve products' nutritional profile.</li><li>Complete the RMPS/RMS review and formulation review for new version of Recipe as per NDC agreed timeline.</li><li>Involve in the reformulation of existing product for optimized quality and process ability and the development of new formulations.</li><li>Ensure active FERT is linked to approved Semi Finished Goods (SFG) specification.</li><li>Maintain BOM material data completeness and accuracy for new product development & reformulation.</li></ol><p><br /><strong>Key Experiences:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Food Science, Technology or a related discipline</li><li>Preferably 3 years’ relevant experience in a manufacturing environment / Food / Pharmaceuticals industry.</li><li>Possess high level of communication and report writing skills</li><li>Must be a team player and able to work independently</li></ul>",
